      "content": "thanks, that's actually super helpful for my outline. i think i get the hang of it. one more thing though—i'm worried my professor might think i'm being too one-sided. if someone were to argue that wealth redistribution is actually \"theft\" or that it's fundamentally unfair to take from people who earned their money through hard work, how would you explain that their view is just logically flawed or outdated compared to the equity argument?",
